  "texts": [
    "Nonetheless, it could also be argued that AI does not provide a perfect substitute for humans in this respect.",
    "An evaluation of Wordvice AI, a proofreading tool, highlighted that the tool could outperform the built-in proofreading abilities of Google Docs or Microsoft Word, but still only managed to identify 77% of what was identified by a human proofreader (Heintz et al., 2022).",
    "While AI may be able to support typos, spelling errors, and grammar mistakes, it fails to grasp nuance or a writer's intent.",
    "These studies successfully highlight a general awareness and use of AI technologies to support writing among students, they fail to specifically explore the context of use by ESL students, leaving a gap in the literature regarding the use of AI to support students for whom English is not their primary language.",
    "Second, some students may find it difficult to synthesize research, develop a coherent argument, conduct a literature review, or contribute to the scholarly body of knowledge (Malik et al., 2023)."
  ],
